# ecoData — Sustainable Liquid Cooling for Data Centers

A digital twin simulator and sustainability demonstration for a closed-loop 
liquid cooling system designed to reduce water consumption, energy usage, 
and thermal inefficiency in modern data centers.

## What This Is
ecoData models a GPU/CPU → Cold Plate → Pump → Heat Exchanger → Radiator 
cooling loop using real thermal physics (Q = ṁ · Cₚ · ΔT). 
The interactive web demo lets you adjust system parameters and watch 
live calculations update in real time.

## Features
- Live physics simulator (GPU power, flow rate, ambient temp inputs)
- Real-time outputs: junction temp, coolant inlet/outlet, PUE score
- Animated cooling loop visualization
- Water usage comparison: Traditional vs ecoData (fresh + grey water)
- Scale simulation: single server → full data center

## Status
- [x] Phase 1 — Digital twin simulator (complete)
- [ ] Phase 2 — Physical prototype (~$150 Arduino build)
- [ ] Phase 3 — Rack-scale cooling module
- [ ] Phase 4 — AI-optimized cooling platform


## Tech
HTML · CSS · JavaScript · Chart.js · Thermal Physics Modeling

## Goal
Reduce data center water usage by ~90% using closed-loop grey water 
recirculation — validated by digital twin before physical build.
